This Dunkin‘ Donuts has been under new management now for a few years (about 3? I think), and the quality of the food is very, very good :-)  Moreover, and why I’m writing this, Their customer service is EXCELLENT.  My boyfriend and I have both noticed individually of each other that if you’re a regular here, they really get to know you and exactly what you like and how you like it.  They’re incredibly friendly and KIND.  I have to mention something that happened to me 10 days ago.  Around 3:30AM - 4AM, I was EXTREMELY SICK and DESPERATELY NEEDED an ambulance to take me to the hospital.  I didn’t have access to a working phone at my house and knew that this Dunkin‘ Donuts, which is only a block and a half away from my home, is open 24/7.  Hunched and looking like a deathly spectre, I hobbled over to their store and asked the man behind the counter who appeared to be the manager or owner - and Who actually DIDN’T KNOW ME AT ALL, so had no reason to treat me in a special way as a regular - to call for an ambulance.  He immediately told the other man working there to call 911.  As the weather outside was decent, I told him I would wait at one of the tables arranged outside.  After they called, he came outside to reassure me that the 911 operator said the ambulance would arrive in 4 minutes.  It did.  And thank goodness for it.  If you read my reviews, you will see that I don’t bother to write them very often - someone has to be either REALLY GOOD to me or REALLY BAD to me for me to bother to organize my thoughts into a cohesive paragraph for others to read.  But in this case, I have to acknowledge this Dunkin‘ Donuts, not only for its very good food, but for the excellent character of the good caring community members who work there.  The only reason it’s taken me 10 days to write is I’ve been fighting this darned illness the whole time :-)
